<title type="html"><![CDATA[Save feature]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6999&amp;p=68059#p68059"><![CDATA[
It's much easier to port a Disk System game to the NES if you give it WRAM.  In Zelda, most of the WRAM is devoted to holding a code bank, very little of it is for saved games.  And the prototype version of SMB2 was MMC1 with WRAM and CHR RAM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Sun Oct 03, 2010 6:17 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
